<paragraph blockId="41.[264,935,804,865]" box="[264,420,839,865]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
(
<figureCitation box="[273,412,839,865]" captionStart="FIGURES 81–84" captionStartId="41.[264,382,1819,1843]" captionTargetBox="[265,1323,1199,1788]" captionTargetId="figure-252@41.[259,1348,1179,1806]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="FIGURES 81–84. Robustagramma rarum sp. nov.: 81, posterior view of male terminalia; 82, lateral view of male terminalia; 83, lateral view of male internal genitalia; 84, male sternite 5." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5049863" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5049863/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Figs. 81–84</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="41.[264,1323,919,1105]" box="[264,997,919,945]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
As described for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Marshall &amp; Cui" authorityYear="2005" box="[465,778,919,944]" class="Insecta" family="Sphaeroceridae" genus="Robustagramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="binitidum">
<emphasis box="[465,778,919,944]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Robustagramma binitidum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
except as follows.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="41.[264,1323,919,1105]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
Body length 
<quantity box="[457,551,959,985]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" unit="mm" value="1.7">1.7 mm</quantity>
. General color dark brown. Gena and lower frons reddish brown; face and antenna brown. Two orbital bristles, anterior orbital bristle small (most head bristles of unique 
<typeStatus box="[432,482,1039,1065]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">type</typeStatus>
damaged or lost). Postvertical bristles similar in size to anterior orbital bristle. Postocellar bristles weak. Eye height 
<emphasis box="[791,819,1079,1104]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">ca</emphasis>
. 2.6 times genal height.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5049863" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5049863" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5049863/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" startId="41.[264,382,1819,1843]" targetBox="[265,1323,1199,1788]" targetPageId="41">
<paragraph blockId="41.[264,1322,1819,1877]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[264,462,1819,1843]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">FIGURES 81–84.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Marshall &amp; Cui, 2005" authorityName="Marshall &amp; Cui" authorityYear="2005" box="[471,722,1819,1842]" class="Insecta" family="Sphaeroceridae" genus="Robustagramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rarum" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[471,722,1819,1842]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Robustagramma rarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[729,817,1819,1842]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
: 81, posterior view of male terminalia; 82, lateral view of male terminalia; 83, lateral view of male internal genitalia; 84, male sternite 5.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="42.[264,1325,284,1070]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
Acrostichal setulae in 6 or 8 irregular rows between anterior dorsocentral bristles. Posterodorsal katepisternal bristle over half as long as distance between bristle base and wing base. Wing with length ratio of second to third costal sectors 
<emphasis box="[980,1008,364,389]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">ca</emphasis>
. 0.56. Discal cell rounded, without appendices. Mid femur of male with two anterior subapical bristles, 7 ventral proximal bristles and one posterodorsal apical bristles.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="42.[264,1325,284,1070]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
Male terminalia: Sternite 5 
<emphasis box="[641,669,484,509]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">ca</emphasis>
. 1.5 times as long as sternite 4, with many dark, clublike scales on posteromedial margin, two patches of short, stout bristles on central area, and a borderline between pale posterocentral area and dark anterior area; without shining patches. Dorsomedial length of epandrium 
<emphasis box="[809,837,604,629]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">ca</emphasis>
. 0.25X length of sternite 8. Surstylus entirely setose; cerci cuneate, shorter than surstylus. Ejaculatory apodeme small.
</paragraph>
